@Eliteninjasauce: Thanks for the response.  

But now I wonder how it would play out if you [Fling](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fling) in response to a [Soul's Fire](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Soul's Fire) or a [Boros Fury-Shield](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Boros Fury-Shield) being played on your creature. I recall reading the rules that for a spell to play out completely it must have a valid target upon casting AND when it resolves. But I hear people talking about "last known power on the battlefield" as well.  

If I attack with a creature and my opponent uses [Boros Fury-Shield](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Boros Fury-Shield) on it and I respond with [Fling](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fling) before the fury-shield resolves, do I take damage from the fury-shield?
